  "text": "Because CYP-derived EETs transactivate the EGF receptor, [CITATION_1] which has been linked to an increase in COX-2 expression, [CITATION_2] the aim of the present investigation was to determine whether an increase in CYP2C9 expression and activity could elicit an increase in COX-2 expression and whether COX-2 is involved in CYP2C9-induced angiogenesis.",
